1	//! PEP 508 markers implementations with validation and warnings
2	//!
3	//! Markers allow you to install dependencies only in specific environments (python version,
4	//! operating system, architecture, etc.) or when a specific feature is activated. E.g. you can
5	//! say `importlib-metadata ; python_version < "3.8"` or
6	//! `itsdangerous (>=1.1.0) ; extra == 'security'`. Unfortunately, the marker grammar has some
7	//! oversights (e.g. <https://github.com/pypa/packaging.python.org/pull/1181>) and
8	//! the design of comparisons (PEP 440 comparisons with lexicographic fallback) leads to confusing
9	//! outcomes. This implementation tries to carefully validate everything and emit warnings whenever
10	//! bogus comparisons with unintended semantics are made.
