33	    // While it has not been positively observed, we sort the files
34	    // to ensure we have a defined ordering. Otherwise, if we rely on
35	    // the API to provide a stable ordering and doesn't, it can lead
36	    // non-deterministic behavior elsewhere. (This is somewhat hand-wavy
37	    // and a bit of a band-aide, since arguably, the order of this API
38	    // response probably shouldn't have an impact on things downstream from
39	    // this. That is, if something depends on ordering, then it should
40	    // probably be the thing that does the sorting.)
41	    files.sort_unstable_by(|f1, f2| f1.filename.cmp(&f2.filename));
42	    Ok(files)
43	}
